built with pdoc

aiobungie

A statically typed, asynchronous API wrapper for building clients for Bungie's API in Python.

Getting Started

aiobungie provides 3 different client interfaces to get started with, each serve a different purpose.

  • Client: is probably what you want to get started with first. It provides minimal abstraction for the REST api. Is Pythonic.
  • RESTClient: When you're building a light-weight REST backend. You can use this one. It returns JSON objects instead of dataclasses, as well OAuth2 API. This is considered lower-level version of Client.
  • RESTPool: when you're serving a large amount of users and want to spawn a session for each. each instance of this pool returns a RESTClient.

Check either the examples or each of those objects's documentation for more information about the usage.

23"""A statically typed, asynchronous API wrapper for building clients for Bungie's API in Python.
24
25### Getting Started
26
27aiobungie provides 3 different client interfaces to get started with, each serve a different purpose.
28
29* `Client`: is probably what you want to get started with first. It provides minimal abstraction for the REST api. Is [Pythonic](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/84102/what-is-idiomatic-code#84270).
30* `RESTClient`: When you're building a light-weight REST backend. You can use this one. It returns `JSON` objects instead of `dataclasses`, as well `OAuth2` API.
31This is considered lower-level version of `Client`.
32* `RESTPool`: when you're serving a large amount of users and want to spawn a session for each. each instance of this pool returns a `RESTClient`.
33
34Check either the examples or each of those objects's documentation for more information about the usage.
35"""

class Client(aiobungie.traits.Compact): 
  55class Client(traits.Compact):
  56    """Compact standard client implementation.
  57
  58    This client is the way to be able to start sending requests over the REST API and receiving deserialized response objects.
  59
  60    Refer to `aiobungie.RESTClient` if you prefer to use a more lower-level client.
  61
  62    Example
  63    -------
  64    ```py
  65    import aiobungie
  66    import asyncio
  67
  68    async def main():
  69        client = aiobungie.Client('token')
  70        async with client.rest:
  71            user = await client.fetch_bungie_user(20315338)
  72            print(user)
  73
  74    asyncio.run(main())
  75    ```
  76
  77    Parameters
  78    -----------
  79    token: `str`
  80        Your Bungie's API key or Token from the developer's portal.
  81
  82    Other Parameters
  83    ----------------
  84    max_retries : `int`
  85        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `5xx` status code.
  86    client_secret : `str | None`
  87        An optional application client secret,
  88        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  89    client_id : `int | None`
  90        An optional application client id,
  91        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  92    debug: `"TRACE" | bool | int`
  93        The level of logging to enable.
  94    """
  95
  96    __slots__ = ("_rest", "_framework")
  97
  98    def __init__(
  99        self,
 100        token: str,
 101        /,
 102        *,
 103        client_secret: str | None = None,
 104        client_id: int | None = None,
 105        max_retries: int = 4,
 106        debug: typing.Literal["TRACE"] | bool | int = False,
 107    ) -> None:
 108        self._rest = rest_.RESTClient(
 109            token,
 110            client_secret=client_secret,
 111            client_id=client_id,
 112            max_retries=max_retries,
 113            debug=debug,
 114        )
 115
 116        self._framework = framework.Framework()
 117
 118    @property
 119    def framework(self) -> api.Framework:
 120        return self._framework
 121
 122    @property
 123    def rest(self) -> api.RESTClient:
 124        return self._rest
 125
 126    @property
 127    def request(self) -> Client:
 128        return self
 129
 130    @property
 131    def metadata(self) -> collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any]:
 132        return self._rest.metadata
 133

 136    async def fetch_current_user_memberships(self, access_token: str, /) -> user.User:
 137        """Fetch and return a user object of the bungie net user associated with account.
 138
 139        .. warning::
 140            This method requires OAuth2 scope and a Bearer access token.
 141
 142        Parameters
 143        ----------
 144        access_token : `str`
 145            A valid Bearer access token for the authorization.
 146
 147        Returns
 148        -------
 149        `aiobungie.crates.user.User`
 150            A user object includes the Destiny memberships and Bungie.net user.
 151        """
 152        resp = await self.rest.fetch_current_user_memberships(access_token)
 153
 154        return self._framework.deserialize_user(resp)

 177    async def search_users(
 178        self, name: str, /
 179    ) -> sain.Iterator[user.SearchableDestinyUser]:
 180        """Search for players and return all players that matches the same name.

 323    async def fetch_profile(
 324        self,
 325        member_id: int,
 326        type: enums.MembershipType | int,
 327        components: collections.Sequence[enums.ComponentType],
 328        auth: str | None = None,
 329    ) -> components.Component:
 330        """Fetch a Bungie profile with the required components.
 331
 332        Example
 333        -------
 334        ```py
 335        my_profile_id = 4611686018484639825
 336        my_profile = await client.fetch_profile(
 337            my_profile_id,
 338            MembershipType.STEAM,
 339            components=(ComponentType.CHARACTERS,)
 340        )
 341        characters = my_profile.characters
 342        if characters is not None:
 343            for character in characters.values():
 344                print(character.power_level)
 345        ```
 346
 347        Parameters
 348        ----------
 349        member_id: `int`
 350            The profile membership's id.
 351        type: `aiobungie.MembershipType`
 352            The profile's membership type.
 353        components : `collections.Sequence[aiobungie.ComponentType]`
 354            A sequence of components to collect. If the sequence is empty, then all components will be `None`.
 355
 356        Other Parameters
 357        ----------------
 358        auth : `str | None`
 359            A Bearer access_token to make the request with.
 360            This is optional and limited to components that only requires an Authorization token.
 361
 362        Returns
 363        --------
 364        `aiobungie.crates.Component`
 365            A Destiny 2 player profile with its components.
 366            Only passed components will be available if they exists. Otherwise they will be `None`
 367
 368        Raises
 369        ------
 370        `aiobungie.MembershipTypeError`
 371            The provided membership type was invalid.
 372        """
 373        data = await self.rest.fetch_profile(member_id, type, components, auth)
 374        return self._framework.deserialize_components(data)

 376    async def fetch_linked_profiles(
 377        self,
 378        member_id: int,
 379        member_type: enums.MembershipType | int,
 380        /,
 381        *,
 382        all: bool = False,
 383    ) -> profile.LinkedProfile:
 384        """Returns a summary information about all profiles linked to the requested member.
 385
 386        The passed membership id/type maybe a Bungie.Net membership or a Destiny memberships.
 387
 388        .. note::
 389            It will only return linked accounts whose linkages you are allowed to view.
 390
 391        Parameters
 392        ----------
 393        member_id : `int`
 394            The ID of the membership. This must be a valid Bungie.Net or PSN or Xbox ID.
 395        member_type : `aiobungie.MembershipType`
 396            The type for the membership whose linked Destiny account you want to return.
 397
 398        Other Parameters
 399        ----------------
 400        all : `bool`
 401            If provided and set to `True`, All memberships regardless
 402            of whether they're obscured by overrides will be returned,
 403
 404            If provided and set to `False`, Only available memberships will be returned.
 405            The default for this is `False`.
 406
 407        Returns
 408        -------
 409        `aiobungie.crates.profile.LinkedProfile`
 410            A linked profile object.
 411        """
 412        resp = await self.rest.fetch_linked_profiles(member_id, member_type, all=all)
 413
 414        return self._framework.deserialize_linked_profiles(resp)

 938    async def search_group(
 939        self,
 940        name: str,
 941        group_type: enums.GroupType | int,
 942        *,
 943        creation_date: clans.GroupDate | int = 0,
 944        sort_by: int | None = None,
 945        group_member_count_filter: typing.Literal[0, 1, 2, 3] | None = None,
 946        locale_filter: str | None = None,
 947        tag_text: str | None = None,
 948        items_per_page: int | None = None,
 949        current_page: int | None = None,
 950        request_token: str | None = None,
 951    ) -> collections.Sequence[clans.Group]:
 952        """Search for groups.
 953
 954        .. note::
 955            If the group type is set to `CLAN`, then parameters `group_member_count_filter`,
 956            `locale_filter` and `tag_text` must be `None`, otherwise `ValueError` will be raised.
 957
 958        Parameters
 959        ----------
 960        name : `str`
 961            The group name.
 962        group_type : `aiobungie.GroupType | int`
 963            The group type that's being searched for.
 964
 965        Other Parameters
 966        ----------------
 967        creation_date : `aiobungie.GroupDate | int`
 968            The creation date of the group. Defaults to `0` which is all time.
 969        sort_by : `int | None`
 970            ...
 971        group_member_count_filter : `int | None`
 972            ...
 973        locale_filter : `str | None`
 974            ...
 975        tag_text : `str | None`
 976            ...
 977        items_per_page : `int | None`
 978            ...
 979        current_page : `int | None`
 980            ...
 981        request_token : `str | None`
 982            ...
 983
 984        Returns
 985        --------
 986        `collections.Sequence[aiobungie.crates.Group]`
 987            An array that contains the groups that match the search criteria.
 988
 989        Raises
 990        ------
 991        `ValueError`
 992            If the group type is `aiobungie.GroupType.CLAN` and `group_member_count_filter`,
 993            `locale_filter` and `tag_text` are not `None`.
 994        """
 995        response = await self._rest.search_group(
 996            name,
 997            group_type,
 998            sort_by=sort_by,
 999            creation_date=creation_date,
1000            group_member_count_filter=group_member_count_filter,
1001            locale_filter=locale_filter,
1002            tag_text=tag_text,
1003            items_per_page=items_per_page,
1004            current_page=current_page,
1005            request_token=request_token,
1006        )
1007        return tuple(
1008            self._framework.deserialize_group(result) for result in response["results"]
1009        )

Compact standard client implementation.

This client is the way to be able to start sending requests over the REST API and receiving deserialized response objects.

Refer to RESTClient if you prefer to use a more lower-level client.

Example
import aiobungie
import asyncio

async def main():
    client = Client('token')
    async with client.rest:
        user = await client.fetch_bungie_user(20315338)
        print(user)

asyncio.run(main())
Parameters
  • token (str): Your Bungie's API key or Token from the developer's portal.
Other Parameters
  • max_retries (int): The max retries number to retry if the request hit a 5xx status code.
  • client_secret (str | None): An optional application client secret, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • client_id (int | None): An optional application client id, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • debug ("TRACE" | bool | int): The level of logging to enable.
Client( token: str, /, *, client_secret: str | None = None, client_id: int | None = None, max_retries: int = 4, debug: Union[Literal['TRACE'], bool, int] = False) 
 98    def __init__(
 99        self,
100        token: str,
101        /,
102        *,
103        client_secret: str | None = None,
104        client_id: int | None = None,
105        max_retries: int = 4,
106        debug: typing.Literal["TRACE"] | bool | int = False,
107    ) -> None:
108        self._rest = rest_.RESTClient(
109            token,
110            client_secret=client_secret,
111            client_id=client_id,
112            max_retries=max_retries,
113            debug=debug,
114        )
115
116        self._framework = framework.Framework()

A mutable mapping storage for the user's needs.

1149        activity_type : `aiobungie.aiobungie.crates.FireteamActivity | int`
1150            The fireteam activity type.
1151
1152        Other Parameters
1153        ----------------
1154        platform : `aiobungie.aiobungie.crates.fireteams.FireteamPlatform | int`
1155            If this is provided. Then the results will be filtered with the given platform.
1156            Defaults to `aiobungie.crates.FireteamPlatform.ANY` which returns all platforms.
1157        language : `aiobungie.crates.fireteams.FireteamLanguage | str`
1158            A locale language to filter the used language in that fireteam.
1159            Defaults to `aiobungie.crates.FireteamLanguage.ALL`
1160        date_range : `int`
1161            An integer to filter the date range of the returned fireteams. Defaults to `0`.
1162        page : `int`
1163            The page number. By default its `0` which returns all available activities.
1164        public_only: `bool`
1165            If set to True, Then only public fireteams will be returned.
1166        slots_filter : `int`
1167            Filter the returned fireteams based on available slots. Default is `0`
1168
1169        Returns
1170        -------
1171        `collections.Sequence[aiobungie.crates.Fireteam]`
1172            A sequence of  fireteams found in the clan.
1173            `None` will be returned if nothing was found.
1174        """
1175        resp = await self.rest.fetch_available_clan_fireteams(
1176            access_token,
1177            group_id,
1178            activity_type,
1179            platform=platform,
1180            language=language,
1181            date_range=date_range,
1182            page=page,
1183            public_only=public_only,
1184            slots_filter=slots_filter,
1185        )
1186
1187        return self._framework.deserialize_fireteams(resp)

Fetch a clan's fireteams with open slots.

This method requires OAuth2: ReadGroups scope.

Parameters
  • access_token (str): The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
  • group_id (int): The group/clan id of the fireteam.
  • activity_type (FireteamActivity | int): The fireteam activity type.
Other Parameters
  • platform (FireteamPlatform | int): If this is provided. Then the results will be filtered with the given platform. Defaults to FireteamPlatform.ANY which returns all platforms.
  • language (FireteamLanguage | str): A locale language to filter the used language in that fireteam. Defaults to FireteamLanguage.ALL
  • date_range (int): An integer to filter the date range of the returned fireteams. Defaults to 0.
  • page (int): The page number. By default its 0 which returns all available activities.
  • public_only (bool): If set to True, Then only public fireteams will be returned.
  • slots_filter (int): Filter the returned fireteams based on available slots. Default is 0
Returns
  • collections.Sequence[aiobungie.crates.Fireteam]: A sequence of fireteams found in the clan. None will be returned if nothing was found.

class Flag(enum.Flag): 
 92class Flag(__enum.Flag):
 93    """Builtin Python enum flag with extra handlings."""
 94
 95    # Needs to type this here for mypy
 96    _value_: int
 97
 98    @property
 99    def name(self) -> str:
100        if self._name_ is None:
101            self._name_ = f"UNKNOWN {self._value_}"
102
103        return self._name_
104
105    @property
106    def value(self) -> int:
107        return self._value_
108
109    def __str__(self) -> str:
110        return self.name
111
112    def __repr__(self) -> str:
113        return f"<{type(self).__name__}.{self.name}: {self._value_!s}>"
114
115    def __int__(self) -> int:
116        return int(self.value)
117
118    def __or__(self, other: Flag | int) -> Flag:
119        return self.__class__(self._value_ | int(other))
120
121    def __xor__(self, other: Flag | int) -> Flag:
122        return self.__class__(self._value_ ^ int(other))
123
124    def __and__(self, other: Flag | int) -> Flag:
125        return self.__class__(other & int(other))
126
127    def __invert__(self) -> Flag:
128        return self.__class__(~self._value_)
129
130    def __contains__(self, other: Flag | int) -> bool:
131        return self.value & int(other) == int(other)

58@typing.final
59class GatingScope(int, enums.Enum):
60    """An enum represents restrictive type of gating that is being performed by an entity.

68    CLAN = 2

72    ASSUMED_WORST_CASE = 6

int([x]) -> integer int(x, base=10) -> integer

Convert a number or string to an integer, or return 0 if no arguments are given. If x is a number, return x.__int__(). For floating point numbers, this truncates towards zero.

If x is not a number or if base is given, then x must be a string, bytes, or bytearray instance representing an integer literal in the given base. The literal can be preceded by '+' or '-' and be surrounded by whitespace. The base defaults to 10. Valid bases are 0 and 2-36. Base 0 means to interpret the base from the string as an integer literal.

>>> int('0b100', base=0)

 93    http_status: http.HTTPStatus

 97    """The Bungie response throttle seconds."""

115    """A dict of string key, value that includes each cause of the error
116    to a message describes information about that error.
117    """

119    def __str__(self) -> str:
120        status_name, status_value = (
121            self.http_status.name.replace("_", "").title(),
122            self.http_status.value,
123        )
124        return (
125            f"{status_name}: " + "("
126            f"""
127            http_status: {status_value},
128            message: {self.message if self.message else 'UNDEFINED'},
129            error_status: {self.error_status if self.error_status else 'UNDEFINED'},
130            url: {self.url if self.url else 'UNDEFINED'},
131            message_data: {self.message_data}
132        """ + ")"
133        )

@attrs.define(auto_exc=True)
class MembershipTypeError(aiobungie.BadRequest): 
181@attrs.define(auto_exc=True)
182class MembershipTypeError(BadRequest):
183    """A bad request error raised when passing wrong membership to the request.
184
185    Those fields are useful since it returns the correct membership and id which can be used
186    to make the request again with those fields.
187
188    Example
189    -------
190    ```py
191    try:
192        profile = await client.fetch_profile(
193            member_id=1,
194            type=aiobungie.MembershipType.STADIA,
195            components=()
196        )
197
198    # Membership type is wrong!
199    except aiobungie.MembershipTypeError as err:
200        correct_membership = err.into_membership()
201        profile_id = err.membership_id
202
203        # Recall the method.
204        profile = await client.fetch_profile(
205            member_id=profile_id,
206            type=correct_membership,
207            components=()
208        )
209    ```
210    """
211
212    membership_type: str
213    """The errored membership type passed to the request."""
214
215    membership_id: int
216    """The errored user's membership id."""
217
218    required_membership: str
219    """The required correct membership for errored user."""
220
221    def into_membership(self, value: str | None = None) -> enums.MembershipType:
222        """Turn the required membership from `str` into `aiobungie.Membership` type.
223
224        If value parameter is not provided it will fall back to the required membership.
225        """
226        if value is None:
227            return _MEMBERSHIP_LOOKUP[self.required_membership]
228        return _MEMBERSHIP_LOOKUP[value]
229
230    def __str__(self) -> str:
231        return (
232            f"Expected membership: {self.into_membership().name.replace('_', '').title()}, "
233            f"But got {self.into_membership(self.membership_type)} for id {self.membership_id}"
234        )
235
236    def __int__(self) -> int:
237        return int(self.membership_id)

A bad request error raised when passing wrong membership to the request.

Those fields are useful since it returns the correct membership and id which can be used to make the request again with those fields.

Example
try:
    profile = await client.fetch_profile(
        member_id=1,
        type=MembershipType.STADIA,
        components=()
    )

# Membership type is wrong!
except MembershipTypeError as err:
    correct_membership = err.into_membership()
    profile_id = err.membership_id

    # Recall the method.
    profile = await client.fetch_profile(
        member_id=profile_id,
        type=correct_membership,
        components=()
    )

Convert a number or string to an integer, or return 0 if no arguments are given. If x is a number, return x.__int__(). For floating point numbers, this truncates towards zero.

If x is not a number or if base is given, then x must be a string, bytes, or bytearray instance representing an integer literal in the given base. The literal can be preceded by '+' or '-' and be surrounded by whitespace. The base defaults to 10. Valid bases are 0 and 2-36. Base 0 means to interpret the base from the string as an integer literal.

class RESTClient(aiobungie.api.rest.RESTClient): 
 362class RESTClient(api.RESTClient):
 363    """A single process REST client implementation.
 364
 365    This client is designed to only make HTTP requests and return raw JSON objects.
 366
 367    Example
 368    -------
 369    ```py
 370    import aiobungie
 371
 372    client = aiobungie.RESTClient("TOKEN")
 373    async with client:
 374        response = await client.fetch_clan_members(4389205)
 375        for member in response['results']:
 376            print(member['destinyUserInfo'])
 377    ```
 378
 379    Parameters
 380    ----------
 381    token : `str`
 382        A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
 383
 384    Other Parameters
 385    ----------------
 386    max_retries : `int`
 387        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `5xx` status code.
 388    client_secret : `str | None`
 389        An optional application client secret,
 390        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
 391    client_id : `int | None`
 392        An optional application client id,
 393        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
 394    debug : `bool | str`
 395        Whether to enable logging responses or not.
 396
 397    Logging Levels
 398    --------------
 399    * `False`: This will disable logging.
 400    * `True`: This will set the level to `DEBUG` and enable logging minimal information.
 401    * `"TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE`: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.
 402    """
 403
 404    __slots__ = (
 405        "_token",
 406        "_session",
 407        "_lock",
 408        "_max_retries",
 409        "_client_secret",
 410        "_client_id",
 411        "_metadata",
 412        "_dumps",
 413        "_loads",
 414    )
 415
 416    def __init__(
 417        self,
 418        token: str,
 419        /,
 420        *,
 421        client_secret: str | None = None,
 422        client_id: int | None = None,
 423        client_session: aiohttp.ClientSession | None = None,
 424        dumps: typedefs.Dumps = helpers.dumps,
 425        loads: typedefs.Loads = helpers.loads,
 426        max_retries: int = 4,
 427        debug: typing.Literal["TRACE"] | bool | int = False,
 428    ) -> None:
 429        self._session = client_session
 430        self._lock: asyncio.Lock | None = None
 431        self._client_secret = client_secret
 432        self._client_id = client_id
 433        self._token: str = token
 434        self._max_retries = max_retries
 435        self._dumps = dumps
 436        self._loads = loads
 437        self._metadata: collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any] = {}
 438        self.with_debug(debug)
 439
 440    @property
 441    def client_id(self) -> int | None:
 442        return self._client_id
 443
 444    @property
 445    def metadata(self) -> collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any]:
 446        return self._metadata
 447
 448    @property
 449    def is_alive(self) -> bool:
 450        return self._session is not None
 451
 452    @typing.final
 453    async def close(self) -> None:
 454        if self._session is None:
 455            raise RuntimeError("REST client is not running.")
 456
 457        await self._session.close()
 458        self._session = None
 459
 460    @typing.final
 461    def open(self) -> None:
 462        """Open a new client session. This is called internally with contextmanager usage."""
 463        if self._session:
 464            raise RuntimeError("Cannot open REST client when it's already open.")
 465
 466        self._session = aiohttp.ClientSession(
 467            connector=aiohttp.TCPConnector(),
 468            connector_owner=True,
 469            raise_for_status=False,
 470            timeout=aiohttp.ClientTimeout(total=30.0),
 471        )
 472
 473    @typing.final
 474    async def static_request(
 475        self,
 476        method: _HTTP_METHOD,
 477        path: str,
 478        *,
 479        auth: str | None = None,
 480        json: collections.Mapping[str, typing.Any] | None = None,
 481        params: collections.Mapping[str, typing.Any] | None = None,
 482    ) -> typedefs.JSONIsh:
 483        return await self._request(method, path, auth=auth, json=json, params=params)
 484
 485    @typing.overload
 486    def build_oauth2_url(self, client_id: int) -> builders.OAuthURL: ...
 487
 488    @typing.overload
 489    def build_oauth2_url(self) -> builders.OAuthURL | None: ...
 490
 491    @typing.final
 492    def build_oauth2_url(
 493        self, client_id: int | None = None
 494    ) -> builders.OAuthURL | None:
 495        client_id = client_id or self._client_id
 496        if client_id is None:
 497            return None
 498
 499        return builders.OAuthURL(client_id=client_id)
 500
 501    async def _request(
 502        self,
 503        method: _HTTP_METHOD,
 504        route: str,
 505        *,
 506        base: bool = False,
 507        oauth2: bool = False,
 508        auth: str | None = None,
 509        unwrap_bytes: bool = False,
 510        json: collections.Mapping[str, typing.Any] | None = None,
 511        data: collections.Mapping[str, typing.Any] | None = None,
 512        params: collections.Mapping[str, typing.Any] | None = None,
 513    ) -> typedefs.JSONIsh:
 514        # This is not None when opening the client.
 515        assert self._session is not None, (
 516            "This client hasn't been opened yet. Use `async with client` or `async with client.rest` "
 517            "before performing any request."
 518        )
 519
 520        retries: int = 0
 521        headers: collections.MutableMapping[str, typing.Any] = {}
 522
 523        headers[_USER_AGENT_HEADERS] = _USER_AGENT
 524        headers["X-API-KEY"] = self._token
 525
 526        if auth is not None:
 527            headers[_AUTH_HEADER] = f"Bearer {auth}"
 528
 529        # Handling endpoints
 530        endpoint = url.BASE
 531
 532        if not base:
 533            endpoint = endpoint + url.REST_EP
 534
 535        if oauth2:
 536            assert self._client_id, "Client ID is required to make authorized requests."
 537            assert (
 538                self._client_secret
 539            ), "Client secret is required to make authorized requests."
 540            headers["client_secret"] = self._client_secret
 541
 542            headers["Content-Type"] = "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
 543            endpoint = endpoint + url.TOKEN_EP
 544
 545        if self._lock is None:
 546            self._lock = asyncio.Lock()
 547
 548        if json:
 549            headers["Content-Type"] = _APP_JSON
 550
 551        stack = contextlib.AsyncExitStack()
 552        while True:
 553            try:
 554                await stack.enter_async_context(self._lock)
 555
 556                # We make the request here.
 557                taken_time = time.monotonic()
 558                response = await self._session.request(
 559                    method=method,
 560                    url=f"{endpoint}/{route}",
 561                    headers=headers,
 562                    data=_JSONPayload(json) if json else data,
 563                    params=params,
 564                )
 565                response_time = (time.monotonic() - taken_time) * 1_000
 566
 567                _LOGGER.debug(
 568                    "METHOD: %s ROUTE: %s STATUS: %i ELAPSED: %.4fms",
 569                    method,
 570                    f"{endpoint}/{route}",
 571                    response.status,
 572                    response_time,
 573                )
 574
 575                await self._handle_ratelimit(response, method, route)
 576
 577            except aiohttp.ClientConnectionError as exc:
 578                if retries >= self._max_retries:
 579                    raise error.HTTPError(
 580                        str(exc),
 581                        http.HTTPStatus.SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE,
 582                    )
 583                backoff_ = backoff.ExponentialBackOff(maximum=8)
 584
 585                timer = next(backoff_)
 586                _LOGGER.warning(
 587                    "Client received a connection error <%s> Retrying in %.2fs. Remaining retries: %s",
 588                    type(exc).__qualname__,
 589                    timer,
 590                    self._max_retries - retries,
 591                )
 592                retries += 1
 593                await asyncio.sleep(timer)
 594                continue
 595
 596            finally:
 597                await stack.aclose()
 598
 599            if response.status == http.HTTPStatus.NO_CONTENT:
 600                return None
 601
 602            # Handle the successful response.
 603            if 300 > response.status >= 200:
 604                if unwrap_bytes:
 605                    # We need to read the bytes for the manifest response.
 606                    return await response.read()
 607
 608                # Bungie get funky and return HTML instead of JSON when making an authorized
 609                # request with a dummy access token. We could technically read the page content
 610                # but that's Bungie's fault for not returning a JSON response.
 611                if response.content_type != _APP_JSON:
 612                    raise error.HTTPError(
 613                        message=f"Expected JSON response, Got {response.content_type}, "
 614                        f"{response.real_url.human_repr()}",
 615                        http_status=http.HTTPStatus(response.status),
 616                    )
 617
 618                json_data = self._loads(await response.read())
 619
 620                if _LOGGER.isEnabledFor(TRACE):
 621                    _LOGGER.log(
 622                        TRACE,
 623                        "%s",
 624                        error.stringify_headers(dict(response.headers)),
 625                    )
 626
 627                    details: collections.MutableMapping[str, typing.Any] = {}
 628                    if json:
 629                        details["json"] = json
 630
 631                    if data:
 632                        details["data"] = data
 633
 634                    if params:
 635                        details["params"] = params
 636
 637                    if details:
 638                        _LOGGER.log(TRACE, "%s", error.stringify_headers(details))
 639
 640                # Return the response.
 641                # auth responses are not inside a Response object.
 642                if oauth2:
 643                    return json_data
 644
 645                # The reason we have a type ignore is because the actual response type
 646                # is within this `Response` key.
 647                return json_data["Response"]  # type: ignore
 648
 649            if (
 650                response.status in _RETRY_5XX and retries < self._max_retries  # noqa: W503
 651            ):
 652                backoff_ = backoff.ExponentialBackOff(maximum=6)
 653                sleep_time = next(backoff_)
 654                _LOGGER.warning(
 655                    "Got %i - %s. Sleeping for %.2f seconds. Remaining retries: %i",
 656                    response.status,
 657                    response.reason,
 658                    sleep_time,
 659                    self._max_retries - retries,
 660                )
 661
 662                retries += 1
 663                await asyncio.sleep(sleep_time)
 664                continue
 665
 666            raise await error.panic(response)
 667
 668    async def __aenter__(self) -> RESTClient:
 669        self.open()
 670        return self
 671
 672    async def __aexit__(
 673        self,
 674        exception_type: type[BaseException] | None,
 675        exception: BaseException | None,
 676        exception_traceback: types.TracebackType | None,
 677    ) -> None:
 678        await self.close()
 679
 680    # We don't want this to be super complicated.
 681    @typing.final
 682    async def _handle_ratelimit(
 683        self,
 684        response: aiohttp.ClientResponse,
 685        method: str,
 686        route: str,
 687    ) -> None:
 688        if response.status != http.HTTPStatus.TOO_MANY_REQUESTS:
 689            return
 690
 691        if response.content_type != _APP_JSON:
 692            raise error.HTTPError(
 693                f"Being ratelimited on non JSON request, {response.content_type}.",
 694                http.HTTPStatus.TOO_MANY_REQUESTS,
 695            )
 696
 697        # The reason we have a type ignore here is that we guaranteed the content type is JSON above.
 698        json: typedefs.JSONObject = self._loads(await response.read())  # type: ignore
 699        retry_after = float(json.get("ThrottleSeconds", 15.0)) + 0.1
 700        max_calls: int = 0
 701
 702        while True:
 703            if max_calls == 10:
 704                # Max retries by default. We raise an error here.
 705                raise error.RateLimitedError(
 706                    body=json,
 707                    url=str(response.real_url),
 708                    retry_after=retry_after,
 709                )
 710
 711            # We sleep for a little bit to avoid funky behavior.
 712            _LOGGER.warning(
 713                "We're being ratelimited, Method %s Route %s. Sleeping for %.2fs.",
 714                method,
 715                route,
 716                retry_after,
 717            )
 718            await asyncio.sleep(retry_after)
 719            max_calls += 1
 720            continue
 721
 722    async def fetch_oauth2_tokens(self, code: str, /) -> builders.OAuth2Response:
 723        data = {
 724            "grant_type": "authorization_code",
 725            "code": code,
 726            "client_id": self._client_id,
 727            "client_secret": self._client_secret,
 728        }
 729
 730        response = await self._request(_POST, "", data=data, oauth2=True)
 731        assert isinstance(response, dict)
 732        return builders.OAuth2Response.build_response(response)
 733
 734    async def refresh_access_token(
 735        self, refresh_token: str, /
 736    ) -> builders.OAuth2Response:
 737        data = {
 738            "grant_type": "refresh_token",
 739            "refresh_token": refresh_token,
 740            "client_id": self._client_id,
 741            "client_secret": self._client_secret,
 742        }
 743
 744        response = await self._request(_POST, "", data=data, oauth2=True)
 745        assert isinstance(response, dict)
 746        return builders.OAuth2Response.build_response(response)
 747

 822    async def search_group(
 823        self,
 824        name: str,
 825        group_type: enums.GroupType | int = enums.GroupType.CLAN,
 826        *,
 827        creation_date: clans.GroupDate | int = 0,
 828        sort_by: int | None = None,
 829        group_member_count_filter: typing.Literal[0, 1, 2, 3] | None = None,
 830        locale_filter: str | None = None,
 831        tag_text: str | None = None,
 832        items_per_page: int | None = None,
 833        current_page: int | None = None,
 834        request_token: str | None = None,
 835    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 836        payload: collections.MutableMapping[str, typing.Any] = {"name": name}
 837
 838        # as the official documentation says, you're not allowed to use those fields
 839        # on a clan search. it is safe to send the request with them being `null` but not filled with a value.
 840        if (
 841            group_type == enums.GroupType.CLAN
 842            and group_member_count_filter is not None
 843            and locale_filter
 844            and tag_text
 845        ):
 846            raise ValueError(
 847                "If you're searching for clans, (group_member_count_filter, locale_filter, tag_text) must be None."
 848            )
 849
 850        payload["groupType"] = int(group_type)
 851        payload["creationDate"] = int(creation_date)
 852        payload["sortBy"] = sort_by
 853        payload["groupMemberCount"] = group_member_count_filter
 854        payload["locale"] = locale_filter
 855        payload["tagText"] = tag_text
 856        payload["itemsPerPage"] = items_per_page
 857        payload["currentPage"] = current_page
 858        payload["requestToken"] = request_token
 859        payload["requestContinuationToken"] = request_token
 860
 861        resp = await self._request(_POST, "GroupV2/Search/", json=payload)
 862        assert isinstance(resp, dict)
 863        return resp

1133    async def read_manifest_bytes(self, language: _ALLOWED_LANGS = "en", /) -> bytes:
1134        _ensure_manifest_language(language)
1135
1136        content = await self.fetch_manifest_path()
1137        resp = await self._request(
1138            _GET,
1139            content["mobileWorldContentPaths"][language],
1140            unwrap_bytes=True,
1141            base=True,
1142        )
1143        assert isinstance(resp, bytes)
1144        return resp
1145
1146    async def download_sqlite_manifest(
1147        self,
1148        language: _ALLOWED_LANGS = "en",
1149        name: str = "manifest",
1150        path: pathlib.Path | str = ".",
1151        *,
1152        force: bool = False,
1153        executor: concurrent.futures.Executor | None = None,
1154    ) -> pathlib.Path:
1155        complete_path = _get_path(name, path, sql=True)
1156
1157        if complete_path.exists():
1158            if force:
1159                _LOGGER.info(
1160                    f"Found manifest in {complete_path!s}. Forcing to Re-Download."
1161                )
1162                complete_path.unlink(missing_ok=True)
1163
1164                return await self.download_sqlite_manifest(
1165                    language, name, path, force=force
1166                )
1167
1168            else:
1169                raise FileExistsError(
1170                    "Manifest file already exists, "
1171                    "To force download, set the `force` parameter to `True`."
1172                )
1173
1174        _LOGGER.info(f"Downloading manifest. Location: {complete_path!s}")
1175        data_bytes = await self.read_manifest_bytes(language)
1176        await asyncio.get_running_loop().run_in_executor(
1177            executor, _write_sqlite_bytes, data_bytes, path, name
1178        )
1179        _LOGGER.info("Finished downloading manifest.")
1180        return _get_path(name, path, sql=True)
1181
1182    async def download_json_manifest(
1183        self,
1184        file_name: str = "manifest",
1185        path: str | pathlib.Path = ".",
1186        *,
1187        language: _ALLOWED_LANGS = "en",
1188        executor: concurrent.futures.Executor | None = None,
1189    ) -> pathlib.Path:
1190        _ensure_manifest_language(language)
1191        full_path = _get_path(file_name, path)
1192        _LOGGER.info(f"Downloading manifest JSON to {full_path!r}...")
1193
1194        content = await self.fetch_manifest_path()
1195        json_bytes = await self._request(
1196            _GET,
1197            content["jsonWorldContentPaths"][language],
1198            unwrap_bytes=True,
1199            base=True,
1200        )
1201
1202        assert isinstance(json_bytes, bytes)
1203        await asyncio.get_running_loop().run_in_executor(
1204            executor, _write_json_bytes, json_bytes, file_name, path
1205        )
1206        _LOGGER.info("Finished downloading manifest JSON.")
1207        return full_path
1208

1210        # This is guaranteed str.

2000    async def fetch_topics_page(
2001        self,
2002        category_filter: int,
2003        group: int,
2004        date_filter: int,
2005        sort: str | bytes,
2006        *,
2007        page: int | None = None,
2008        locales: collections.Iterable[str] | None = None,
2009        tag_filter: str | None = None,
2010    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
2011        params = {
2012            "locales": ",".join(locales) if locales is not None else "en",
2013        }
2014        if tag_filter:
2015            params["tagstring"] = tag_filter
2016
2017        resp = await self._request(
2018            _GET,
2019            f"Forum/GetTopicsPaged/{page or 0}/0/{group}/{sort!s}/{date_filter}/{category_filter}/",
2020            params=params,
2021        )
2022        assert isinstance(resp, dict)
2023        return resp

A single process REST client implementation.

This client is designed to only make HTTP requests and return raw JSON objects.

Example
import aiobungie

client = RESTClient("TOKEN")
async with client:
    response = await client.fetch_clan_members(4389205)
    for member in response['results']:
        print(member['destinyUserInfo'])
Parameters
  • token (str): A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
Other Parameters
  • max_retries (int): The max retries number to retry if the request hit a 5xx status code.
  • client_secret (str | None): An optional application client secret, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • client_id (int | None): An optional application client id, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • debug (bool | str): Whether to enable logging responses or not.
Logging Levels
  • False: This will disable logging.
  • True: This will set the level to DEBUG and enable logging minimal information.
  • "TRACE" | TRACE: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.

417        self,
418        token: str,
419        /,
420        *,
421        client_secret: str | None = None,
422        client_id: int | None = None,

424        dumps: typedefs.Dumps = helpers.dumps,
425        loads: typedefs.Loads = helpers.loads,
426        max_retries: int = 4,
427        debug: typing.Literal["TRACE"] | bool | int = False,

A mutable mapping storage for the user's needs.

This mapping is useful for storing any kind of data that the user may need.

Example
import aiobungie

client = RESTClient(…)

async with client:
    # Fetch auth tokens and store them
    client.metadata["tokens"] = await client.fetch_access_token("code")

# Some other time.
async with client:
    # Retrieve the tokens
    tokens: aiobungie.OAuth2Response = client.metadata["tokens"]

    # Use them to fetch your user.
    user = await client.fetch_current_user_memberships(tokens.access_token)
is_alive: bool 
448    @property
449    def is_alive(self) -> bool:
450        return self._session is not None

Returns True if the REST client is alive and False otherwise.

Perform an HTTP request given a valid Bungie endpoint.

This method allows you to freely perform HTTP requests to Bungie's API. It provides authentication support, JSON bodies, URL parameters and out of the box exception handling.

This method is useful for testing routes by yourself. or even calling routes that aiobungie doesn't support yet.

Parameters
  • method (str): The request method, This may be GET, POST, PUT, etc.
  • path (str): The Bungie endpoint or path. A path must look something like this Destiny2/3/Profile/46111239123/...
Other Parameters
  • auth (str | None): An optional bearer token for methods that requires OAuth2 Authorization header.
  • json (MutableMapping[str, typing.Any] | None): An optional JSON mapping to include in the request.
  • params (MutableMapping[str, typing.Any] | None): An optional URL query parameters mapping to include in the request.
Returns
  • aiobungie.typedefs.JSONIsh: The response payload.
@typing.final
def build_oauth2_url(self, client_id: int | None = None) -> aiobungie.builders.OAuthURL | None: 
491    @typing.final
492    def build_oauth2_url(
493        self, client_id: int | None = None
494    ) -> builders.OAuthURL | None:
495        client_id = client_id or self._client_id
496        if client_id is None:
497            return None
498
499        return builders.OAuthURL(client_id=client_id)

Construct a new OAuthURL url object.

You can get the complete string representation of the url by calling .compile() on it.

Parameters
  • client_id (int | None): An optional client id to provide, If left None it will roll back to the id passed to the RESTClient, If both is None this method will return None.
Returns
  • aiobungie.builders.OAuthURL | None: * If client_id was provided as a parameter, It guarantees to return a complete OAuthURL object
    • If client_id is set to RESTClient will be.
    • If both are None this method will return `None.

  • NotFound: The clan was not found.
async def search_group( self, name: str, group_type: GroupType | int = <GroupType.CLAN: 1>, *, creation_date: GroupDate | int = 0, sort_by: int | None = None, group_member_count_filter: Optional[Literal[0, 1, 2, 3]] = None, locale_filter: str | None = None, tag_text: str | None = None, items_per_page: int | None = None, current_page: int | None = None, request_token: str | None = None) -> collections.abc.Mapping[str, typing.Any]: 
822    async def search_group(
823        self,
824        name: str,
825        group_type: enums.GroupType | int = enums.GroupType.CLAN,
826        *,
827        creation_date: clans.GroupDate | int = 0,
828        sort_by: int | None = None,
829        group_member_count_filter: typing.Literal[0, 1, 2, 3] | None = None,
830        locale_filter: str | None = None,
831        tag_text: str | None = None,
832        items_per_page: int | None = None,
833        current_page: int | None = None,
834        request_token: str | None = None,
835    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
836        payload: collections.MutableMapping[str, typing.Any] = {"name": name}
837
838        # as the official documentation says, you're not allowed to use those fields
839        # on a clan search. it is safe to send the request with them being `null` but not filled with a value.
840        if (
841            group_type == enums.GroupType.CLAN
842            and group_member_count_filter is not None
843            and locale_filter
844            and tag_text
845        ):
846            raise ValueError(
847                "If you're searching for clans, (group_member_count_filter, locale_filter, tag_text) must be None."
848            )
849
850        payload["groupType"] = int(group_type)
851        payload["creationDate"] = int(creation_date)
852        payload["sortBy"] = sort_by
853        payload["groupMemberCount"] = group_member_count_filter
854        payload["locale"] = locale_filter
855        payload["tagText"] = tag_text
856        payload["itemsPerPage"] = items_per_page
857        payload["currentPage"] = current_page
858        payload["requestToken"] = request_token
859        payload["requestContinuationToken"] = request_token
860
861        resp = await self._request(_POST, "GroupV2/Search/", json=payload)
862        assert isinstance(resp, dict)
863        return resp

Insert a plug into a socketed item.

OAuth2: AdvancedWriteActions scope is required

Parameters
  • action_token (str): Action token provided by the AwaGetActionToken API call.

    .set_socket_array(0)

)

1154    ) -> pathlib.Path:
1155        complete_path = _get_path(name, path, sql=True)
1156
1157        if complete_path.exists():
1158            if force:
1159                _LOGGER.info(
1160                    f"Found manifest in {complete_path!s}. Forcing to Re-Download."
1161                )
1162                complete_path.unlink(missing_ok=True)
1163
1164                return await self.download_sqlite_manifest(
1165                    language, name, path, force=force
1166                )
1167
1168            else:
1169                raise FileExistsError(
1170                    "Manifest file already exists, "
1171                    "To force download, set the `force` parameter to `True`."
1172                )
1173
1174        _LOGGER.info(f"Downloading manifest. Location: {complete_path!s}")
1175        data_bytes = await self.read_manifest_bytes(language)
1176        await asyncio.get_running_loop().run_in_executor(
1177            executor, _write_sqlite_bytes, data_bytes, path, name
1178        )
1179        _LOGGER.info("Finished downloading manifest.")
1180        return _get_path(name, path, sql=True)

Downloads the SQLite version of Destiny2's Manifest.

Example
manifest = await rest.download_sqlite_manifest()
with sqlite3.connect(manifest) as conn:
    ...
Parameters
  • language (str): The manifest language to download, Default is English.
  • path (str | pathlib.Path): The path to download this manifest. Example "/tmp/databases/", Default is the current directory.
  • name (str): The manifest database file name. Default is manifest
  • force (bool): Whether to force the download. Default is False. However if set to true the old file will get unlinked and a new one will begin to download.
  • executor (concurrent.futures.Executor | None): An optional executor which will be used to write the bytes of the manifest.
Returns
  • pathlib.Path: A pathlib object of the .sqlite file.
Raises
  • FileExistsError: If the manifest file exists and force is False.
  • ValueError: If the provided language was not recognized.

async def awainitialize_request( self, access_token: str, type: Literal[0, 1], membership_type: MembershipType | int, /, *, affected_item_id: int | None = None, character_id: int | None = None) -> collections.abc.Mapping[str, typing.Any]: 
1798    async def awainitialize_request(
1799        self,
1800        access_token: str,
1801        type: typing.Literal[0, 1],
1802        membership_type: enums.MembershipType | int,
1803        /,
1804        *,
1805        affected_item_id: int | None = None,
1806        character_id: int | None = None,
1807    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
1808        body = {"type": type, "membershipType": int(membership_type)}
1809
1810        if affected_item_id is not None:
1811            body["affectedItemId"] = affected_item_id
1812
1813        if character_id is not None:
1814            body["characterId"] = character_id
1815
1816        resp = await self._request(

Initialize a request to perform an advanced write action.

OAuth2: AdvancedWriteActions application scope is required to perform this request.

Parameters
  • access_token (str): The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
  • type (typing.Literal[0, 1]): Type of the advanced write action. Its either 0 or 1. If set to 0 that means it None. Otherwise if 1 that means its insert plugs.
  • membership_type (MembershipType | int): The Destiny membership type of the account to modify.
Other Parameters
  • affected_item_id (int | None): Item instance ID the action shall be applied to. This is optional for all but a new AwaType values.
  • character_id (int | None): The Destiny character ID to perform this action on.

Fetch a Bungie application's API usage.

Parameters
  • access_token (str): The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
  • application_id (int): The application id to get.
Other Parameters

  • start (datetime.datetime | None): A datetime object can be used to collect the start of the application usage. This is limited and can go back to 30 days maximum.

    If this is left to None. It will return the last 24 hours.

  • end (datetime.datetime | None): A datetime object can be used to collect the end of the application usage.

    If this is left to None. It will return now.

Example
import datetime

# Fetch data from 2021 Dec 10th to 2021 Dec 20th
await fetch_application_api_usage(
    start=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 10),
    end=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 20)
)
Returns
  • aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject: A JSON object of the application usage details.

class RESTPool: 
211class RESTPool:
212    """a Pool of `RESTClient` instances.
213
214    This allows to acquire multiple instances of `RESTClient`s which can be acquired with the same token and metadata.
215
216    A full example of this client can be found in the examples directory.
217
218    Example
219    -------
220    ```py
221    import aiobungie
222    import asyncio
223
224    pool = aiobungie.RESTPool("token")
225    pool.metadata['auth_code'] = 'code'
226
227    async def get() -> None:
228        async with pool.acquire() as rest:
229            this = await rest.fetch_current_user_memberships(pool.metadata['auth_code'])
230
231    await asyncio.run(get())
232    ```
233
234    Parameters
235    ----------
236    token : `str`
237        A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
238
239    Other Parameters
240    ----------------
241    max_retries : `int`
242        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `5xx` status code.
243    client_secret : `str | None`
244        An optional application client secret,
245        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
246    client_id : `int | None`
247        An optional application client id,
248        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
249    debug : `bool | str`
250        Whether to enable logging responses or not.
251
252    Logging Levels
253    --------------
254    * `False`: This will disable logging.
255    * `True`: This will set the level to `DEBUG` and enable logging minimal information.
256    Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
257    * `"TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE`: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.
258    """
259
260    __slots__ = (
261        "_token",
262        "_max_retries",
263        "_client_secret",
264        "_client_id",
265        "_metadata",
266        "_enable_debug",
267        "_client_session",
268        "_loads",
269        "_dumps",
270    )
271
272    # Looks like mypy doesn't like this.
273    if typing.TYPE_CHECKING:
274        _enable_debug: typing.Literal["TRACE"] | bool | int
275
276    def __init__(
277        self,
278        token: str,
279        /,
280        *,
281        client_secret: str | None = None,
282        client_id: int | None = None,
283        client_session: aiohttp.ClientSession | None = None,
284        dumps: typedefs.Dumps = helpers.dumps,
285        loads: typedefs.Loads = helpers.loads,
286        max_retries: int = 4,
287        debug: typing.Literal["TRACE"] | bool | int = False,
288    ) -> None:
289        self._client_secret = client_secret
290        self._client_id = client_id
291        self._token = token
292        self._max_retries = max_retries
293        self._metadata: collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any] = {}
294        self._enable_debug = debug
295        self._client_session = client_session
296        self._loads = loads
297        self._dumps = dumps
298
299    @property
300    def client_id(self) -> int | None:
301        return self._client_id
302
303    @property
304    def metadata(self) -> collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any]:
305        """Pool's Metadata. This is different from client instance metadata."""
306        return self._metadata
307
308    @typing.overload
309    def build_oauth2_url(self, client_id: int) -> builders.OAuthURL: ...
310
311    @typing.overload
312    def build_oauth2_url(self) -> builders.OAuthURL | None: ...
313
314    @typing.final
315    def build_oauth2_url(
316        self, client_id: int | None = None
317    ) -> builders.OAuthURL | None:
318        """Construct a new `OAuthURL` url object.
319
320        You can get the complete string representation of the url by calling `.compile()` on it.
321
322        Parameters
323        ----------
324        client_id : `int | None`
325            An optional client id to provide, If left `None` it will roll back to the id passed
326            to the `RESTClient`, If both is `None` this method will return `None`.
327
328        Returns
329        -------
330        `aiobungie.builders.OAuthURL | None`
331            * If `client_id` was provided as a parameter, It guarantees to return a complete `OAuthURL` object
332            * If `client_id` is set to `aiobungie.RESTClient` will be.
333            * If both are `None` this method will return `None.
334        """
335        client_id = client_id or self._client_id
336        if client_id is None:
337            return None
338
339        return builders.OAuthURL(client_id=client_id)
340
341    @typing.final
342    def acquire(self) -> RESTClient:
343        """Acquires a new `RESTClient` instance from this pool.
344
345        Returns
346        -------
347        `RESTClient`
348            An instance of a `RESTClient`.
349        """
350        return RESTClient(
351            self._token,
352            client_secret=self._client_secret,
353            client_id=self._client_id,
354            loads=self._loads,
355            dumps=self._dumps,
356            max_retries=self._max_retries,
357            debug=self._enable_debug,
358            client_session=self._client_session,
359        )

a Pool of RESTClient instances.

This allows to acquire multiple instances of RESTClients which can be acquired with the same token and metadata.

A full example of this client can be found in the examples directory.

Example
import aiobungie
import asyncio

pool = RESTPool("token")
pool.metadata['auth_code'] = 'code'

async def get() -> None:
    async with pool.acquire() as rest:
        this = await rest.fetch_current_user_memberships(pool.metadata['auth_code'])

await asyncio.run(get())

  • token (str): A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
Other Parameters
  • max_retries (int): The max retries number to retry if the request hit a 5xx status code.
  • client_secret (str | None): An optional application client secret, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • client_id (int | None): An optional application client id, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • debug (bool | str): Whether to enable logging responses or not.
Logging Levels
  • False: This will disable logging.
  • True: This will set the level to DEBUG and enable logging minimal information. Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
  • "TRACE" | TRACE: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.

int([x]) -> integer int(x, base=10) -> integer

Convert a number or string to an integer, or return 0 if no arguments are given. If x is a number, return x.__int__(). For floating point numbers, this truncates towards zero.

If x is not a number or if base is given, then x must be a string, bytes, or bytearray instance representing an integer literal in the given base. The literal can be preceded by '+' or '-' and be surrounded by whitespace. The base defaults to 10. Valid bases are 0 and 2-36. Base 0 means to interpret the base from the string as an integer literal.

>>> int('0b100', base=0)

annotations = _Feature((3, 7, 0, 'beta', 1), None, 16777216)
async def panic( response: aiohttp.client_reqrep.ClientResponse) -> HTTPError: 
281async def panic(response: aiohttp.ClientResponse) -> HTTPError:
282    """Immediately raise an exception based on the response."""
283
284    # Bungie get funky and return HTML instead of JSON when making an authorized
285    # request with a dummy access token. We could technically read the page content
286    # but that's Bungie's fault for not returning a JSON response.
287    if response.content_type != "application/json":
288        raise HTTPError(
289            message=f"Expected JSON response, Got {response.content_type}, "
290            f"{response.real_url.human_repr()}",
291            http_status=http.HTTPStatus(response.status),
292        )
293
294    body: collections.Mapping[str, typing.Any] = helpers.loads(await response.read())  # type: ignore
295    message: str = body.get("Message", "UNDEFINED_MESSAGE")
296    error_status: str = body.get("ErrorStatus", "UNDEFINED_ERROR_STATUS")
297    message_data: dict[str, str] = body.get("MessageData", {})
298    throttle_seconds: int = body.get("ThrottleSeconds", 0)
299    error_code: int = body.get("ErrorCode", 0)
300
301    # Standard HTTP status.
302    match response.status:
303        case http.HTTPStatus.NOT_FOUND:
304            return NotFound(
305                message=message,
306                error_code=error_code,
307                throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
308                url=str(response.real_url),
309                body=body,
310                headers=response.headers,
311                error_status=error_status,
312                message_data=message_data,
313            )
314
315        case http.HTTPStatus.FORBIDDEN:
316            return Forbidden(
317                message=message,
318                error_code=error_code,
319                throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
320                url=str(response.real_url),
321                body=body,
322                headers=response.headers,
323                error_status=error_status,
324                message_data=message_data,
325            )
326
327        case http.HTTPStatus.UNAUTHORIZED:
328            return Unauthorized(
329                message=message,
330                error_code=error_code,
331                throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
332                url=str(response.real_url),
333                body=body,
334                headers=response.headers,
335                error_status=error_status,
336                message_data=message_data,
337            )
338
339        case http.HTTPStatus.BAD_REQUEST:
340            # Membership needs to be alone.
341            if error_status == "InvalidParameters":
342                return MembershipTypeError(
343                    message=message,
344                    body=body,
345                    headers=response.headers,
346                    url=str(response.url),
347                    membership_type=message_data["membershipType"],
348                    required_membership=message_data["membershipInfo.membershipType"],
349                    membership_id=int(message_data["membershipId"]),
350                )
351            return BadRequest(
352                message=message,
353                body=body,
354                headers=response.headers,
355                url=str(response.url),
356            )
357        case _:
358            status = http.HTTPStatus(response.status)
359
360            if 400 <= status < 500:
361                return ResponseError(
362                    message=message,
363                    error_code=error_code,
364                    throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
365                    url=str(response.real_url),
366                    body=body,
367                    headers=response.headers,
368                    error_status=error_status,
369                    message_data=message_data,
370                    http_status=status,
371                )
372
373            # Need to self handle ~5xx errors
374            elif 500 <= status < 600:
375                # No API key or method requires OAuth2 most likely.
376                if error_status in {
377                    "ApiKeyMissingFromRequest",
378                    "WebAuthRequired",
379                    "ApiInvalidOrExpiredKey",
380                    "AuthenticationInvalid",
381                    "AuthorizationCodeInvalid",
382                }:
383                    return Unauthorized(
384                        message=message,
385                        error_code=error_code,
386                        throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
387                        url=str(response.real_url),
388                        body=body,
389                        headers=response.headers,
390                        error_status=error_status,
391                        message_data=message_data,
392                    )
393
394                # Anything contains not found.
395                elif (
396                    "NotFound" in error_status
397                    or error_status == "UserCannotFindRequestedUser"
398                ):
399                    return NotFound(
400                        message=message,
401                        error_code=error_code,
402                        throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
403                        url=str(response.real_url),
404                        body=body,
405                        headers=response.headers,
406                        error_status=error_status,
407                        message_data=message_data,
408                    )
409
410                # Other 5xx errors.
411                else:
412                    return InternalServerError(
413                        message=message,
414                        error_code=error_code,
415                        throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
416                        url=str(response.real_url),
417                        body=body,
418                        headers=response.headers,
419                        error_status=error_status,
420                        message_data=message_data,
421                        http_status=status,
422                    )
423            # Something else.
424            else:
425                return HTTPException(
426                    message=message,
427                    error_code=error_code,
428                    throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
429                    url=str(response.real_url),
430                    body=body,
431                    headers=response.headers,
432                    error_status=error_status,
433                    message_data=message_data,
434                    http_status=status,
435                )

Immediately raise an exception based on the response.

def stringify_headers(headers: collections.abc.Mapping[str, typing.Any]) -> str: 
438def stringify_headers(headers: collections.Mapping[str, typing.Any]) -> str:
439    return (
440        "{ \n"
441        + "\n".join(  # noqa: W503
442            f"{f'   {key}'}: {value}"
443            if key
444            not in {
445                "Authorization",
446                "X-API-KEY",
447                "client_secret",
448                "client_id",
449                "access_token",
450                "refresh_token",
451            }
452            else f"   {key}: REDACTED_TOKEN"
453            for key, value in headers.items()
454        )
455        + "\n}"  # noqa: W503
456    )
